---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import threeGenKitchenImg from '../assets/images/three-gen-kitchen.jpg';
import vintageFoundersImg from '../assets/images/vintage-founders.jpg';
import oldStorefrontImg from '../assets/images/old-storefront.jpg';
import familyCelebrationImg from '../assets/images/family-celebration.jpg';
import bethelParkStoreImg from '../assets/images/bethel-park-store.jpg';
import threeGenerationsImg from '../assets/images/three-generations.jpg';
---
<Layout title="Our Story — Bethel Bakery" description="Three generations of the Walsh family have been baking life sweeter since 1955. From three garages in Bethel Park to two South Hills locations." darkHeader={true} canonicalPath="/about/">

<section class="about-hero">
  <div class="about-hero-overlay"></div>
  <Image src={threeGenKitchenImg} alt="Three generations of Walsh family bakers — Stephen, Morris, and John Walsh in the Bethel Bakery kitchen" class="about-hero-img" width={1024} height={860} loading="eager" />
  <div class="about-hero-content">
    <span class="about-hero-label">Our Story</span>
    <h1>Three Generations of<br />Baking Life Sweeter</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="timeline">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="timeline-block reveal">
      <div class="timeline-media">
        <Image src={vintageFoundersImg} alt="Morris and Anna Walsh at Bethel Bakery, 1961" width={400} height={560} loading="lazy" />
        <span class="timeline-year" aria-hidden="true">1955</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-text">
        <h2>It started in three garages</h2>
        <p>Morris "Moe" Walsh was orphaned at ten and raised by his aunt and uncle on a farm in Bethel Park. After his aunt took a part-time job at Dudt's Bakery in Mt. Lebanon, Morris started working there too. He learned to bake with the same determination that defined everything he did.</p>
        <p>After serving in the U.S. Navy during the Korean War, Morris put $2,500 together with the support of his fiance, Anna Stockhausen. Bethel Bakery began in three attached garages on South Park Road, with parking for two cars.</p>
        <p>Morris started every day at 2 a.m. and worked until 6:30 p.m., six days a week. Sundays were for church and family.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-block timeline-block--reverse reveal">
      <div class="timeline-media">
        <Image src={oldStorefrontImg} alt="The Bethel Bakery storefront on Brightwood Road, rebuilt after the 1992 fire" width={500} height={400} loading="lazy" />
        <span class="timeline-year" aria-hidden="true">1958</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-text">
        <h2>Brightwood Road</h2>
        <p>Three years in, with a small team of employees, Morris moved the bakery to 5200 Brightwood Road, its current Bethel Park home. Through hard work and perseverance, Morris and Anna turned their modest operation into a neighborhood institution.</p>
        <p>Their family grew to seven children: John, Tom, Karen, Susanne, Marianne, Kathleen, and Christine. Every one of them found their place in the bakery and helped it grow.</p>
        <p>Bethel Bakery became known for scratch baking, beautifully decorated cakes, and their famous French Buttercream, made from scratch and still a signature today.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-block reveal">
      <div class="timeline-media">
        <Image src={familyCelebrationImg} alt="The Walsh family celebrating Bethel Bakery's 60th anniversary" width={600} height={500} loading="lazy" />
        <span class="timeline-year" aria-hidden="true">1991</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-text">
        <h2>Second generation</h2>
        <p>Morris and Anna passed the bakery to John, their oldest son, and his wife Chris. John had managed the cake decorating department and found his passion while demonstrating at the National Retail Bakery convention.</p>
        <p>John and Chris brought four children of their own into the business: Patty, Cami, Maria, and Stephen. The next generation of Walshes grew up surrounded by buttercream and flour.</p>
        <p>In November 1992, a fire threatened everything. But the bakery came back stronger: a new storefront, picture images on cakes, and in 2000, one of the first bakery e-commerce websites in the region.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-block timeline-block--reverse reveal">
      <div class="timeline-media">
        <Image src={bethelParkStoreImg} alt="Bethel Bakery storefront in Bethel Park" width={768} height={586} loading="lazy" />
        <span class="timeline-year" aria-hidden="true">2006</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-text">
        <h2>Part of Pittsburgh</h2>
        <p>Bethel Bakery became officially licensed to bake an iced shortbread Terrible Towel cookie, with proceeds going to Merakey Allegheny Valley School. That same year, the bakery was featured in Rick Sebak's WQED documentary "What Makes Pittsburgh, Pittsburgh."</p>
        <p>In 2016, a second location opened at 2500 Washington Road in North Strabane Township, bringing Bethel Bakery to more families in the South Hills.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="timeline-block reveal">
      <div class="timeline-media">
        <Image src={threeGenerationsImg} alt="Stephen Walsh, Morris Walsh, and John Walsh — three generations standing outside Bethel Bakery" width={500} height={630} loading="lazy" />
        <span class="timeline-year" aria-hidden="true">2023</span>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-text">
        <h2>Third generation</h2>
        <p>On July 1, 2023, Stephen Walsh and his wife Kate took the reins. Stephen grew up in the bakery, spent time in the supply chain industry, then returned to spend four years in operations before buying the business from his parents.</p>
        <p>Three generations. Seventy years. The same Brightwood Road kitchen. The same scratch recipes. The same commitment that started with a 20-year-old orphan who woke up at 2 a.m. because he believed baking could be something extraordinary.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="mission">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="mission-inner reveal">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <blockquote>
        Bethel Bakery serves our families, employees, community, and God by preparing baked goods of exceptional quality that bring a special joy to life.
      </blockquote>
      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value">
          <h3>Accountability</h3>
          <p>We acknowledge and accept responsibility for our actions, products, decisions, and policies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value">
          <h3>Commitment</h3>
          <p>We are committed to providing exceptional products and service that exceed expectations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value">
          <h3>Integrity</h3>
          <p>We conduct business with honesty, transparency, and the highest ethical standards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value">
          <h3>Teamwork</h3>
          <p>We work hard, we support each other, and we have fun doing it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero — full bleed photo with overlay */
  .about-hero {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 75vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-hero-img {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 30%;
  }

  .about-hero-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to top,
      oklch(0.15 0.05 250 / 0.85) 0%,
      oklch(0.15 0.05 250 / 0.3) 50%,
      oklch(0.15 0.05 250 / 0.15) 100%
    );
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .about-hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--gutter) var(--space-lg);
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin-inline: auto;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .about-hero-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--rose);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    color: var(--cream);
    max-width: 16ch;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  }

  .timeline-block {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .timeline-block:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .timeline-block--reverse {
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 2fr;
  }

  .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-media {
    order: 2;
  }

  .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-text {
    order: 1;
  }

  .timeline-media {
    position: relative;
  }

  .timeline-media img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 6px;
    aspect-ratio: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .timeline-year {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1.5rem;
    right: -1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--navy);
    opacity: 0.12;
    line-height: 1;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-year {
    right: auto;
    left: -1rem;
  }

  .timeline-text {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .timeline-text h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .timeline-text p {
    color: var(--text-mid);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  .timeline-text p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* Mission */
  .mission {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    background: var(--navy-deep);
    color: var(--cream);
  }

  .mission-inner {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .mission h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .mission blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.2vw, 1.6rem);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 50ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-md);
    text-align: left;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .value h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--rose);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .value p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    opacity: 0.65;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero { min-height: 55vh; }

    .timeline-block,
    .timeline-block--reverse {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-media,
    .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-text {
      order: unset;
    }

    .timeline-year {
      font-size: clamp(3rem, 15vw, 5rem);
      right: 0;
      bottom: -1rem;
    }

    .timeline-block--reverse .timeline-year {
      left: auto;
      right: 0;
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
